The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Dhaka train

 New Delhi, Aug. 3: The train to Dhaka will chug out of Calcuttas Chitpur station by Ramazan in mid-September, reports our special correspondent.

 The journey will be twice a week to start with, home secretary Madhukar Gupta said after the conclusion of two-day talks.

 The first stop will be Gede on the Bangladesh border for customs clearance and security checks. 

 After entering Bangladesh, the train will travel through Jessore, Mymensingh, Pabna and Tangail before entering Dhaka district.




